You know you can rename M4v to MP4 in windows, just right click and rename provided you have the ext showing in windows. It makes no major difference, i had to do it with quite a few files in the past as although my media player would play M4v to would not fastforward or rewind so i renamed them to Mp4 and voila it solved the problem. 

As far as R5 is concerned R stands for Region5 which is russia and surrounding areas. So its a russian dvd(so the picture should be dvd quality) but they have to get rid of the audio and sub with english audio which is either from a cam or the headphone jack in a cinema(line audio) or a screener or whatever but sometimes the russian version of a movie is not exactly the same as the american version which is why with an R5 you might get the audio going in and out of sync at a couple of points in the movie. Hope this helps.

R5 is region 5, encoded with professional tools, better video quality.
